  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Marketing Executive",
  "description": "<h2>Company Overview</h2><p>Our company is engaged in the export and trading of motor vehicles, including sales to overseas markets, coordination of vehicle documentation, and handling of customs clearance processes in Singapore. We work closely with logistics partners, shipping agents, and regulatory bodies to ensure smooth and compliant export operations.</p><h2>Job Responsibilities</h2><ul><li><p>Actively source and develop new customers for vehicle sales, including overseas buyers and dealers</p></li><li><p>Manage end-to-end sales process for vehicle exports, from inquiry to order confirmation and delivery</p></li><li><p>Prepare quotations, negotiate pricing, and close sales deals</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with internal teams and external partners on vehicle availability, shipping schedules, and documentation</p></li><li><p>Handle and follow up on export-related documents such as invoices, packing lists, COO, and export permits</p></li><li><p>Liaise with freight forwarders, shipping lines, and customs agents to ensure smooth customs clearance</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with Singapore customs, LTA, and export regulations</p></li><li><p>Maintain strong relationships with existing clients and provide after-sales support</p></li><li><p>Monitor market trends, pricing, and competitor activities</p></li><li><p>Prepare sales reports and achieve monthly sales targets</p></li></ul>",
